  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(6-23) The twenty-four houses of the Levites.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(6) And David divided them into courses.—Heb., he divided him them (reflexive form of verb, with suffix) into divisions. (Comp. 1Chronicles 24:3, and Genesis 14:15.) Others read the simple voice of the verb here, as at 1Chronicles 24:4-5, 2Chronicles 23:18, Nehemiah 9:22; others, again, the intensive voice, as at 1Chronicles 16:3 (only). It is a question of pointing, the consonants remaining the same in each form. “David divided them,” i.e., the 2,400 superintendents (1Chronicles 23:4; comp. 1Chronicles 23:24). Many of the names here enumerated recur in 1Chronicles 24:20-31; 1Chronicles 26:20-28; whereas the names of the courses of musicians (1Chronicles 25:1-31), warders (1Chronicles 26:1-19), and scribes and judges (1Chronicles 26:29-32), are totally different.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(6) ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "And David divided them into courses.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Heb., ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "he divided him them",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " (reflexive form of verb, with suffix) ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "into divisions.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " (Comp. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Chronicles 24:3",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", and ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Genesis 14:15",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".) Others read the simple voice of the verb here, as at ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
